FOUR teens were killed in a horror smash as they walked home on Sunday at about 4am after partying at a local tavern. Speaking from his hospital bed, Bheki Kubayi (18) &ndash; one of the survivors of the group of 10 friends &ndash; told Daily Sun: &ldquo;We were walking on the road. &ldquo;Instead of passing, a bakkie suddenly lost control and hit us, throwing us into the air! It dragged and killed three boys who were trapped underneath, before coming to a stop against a nearby creche wall.&rdquo; The victims were all schoolkids aged between 12 and 18 years from Hluvukani in the Greater Manyeleti area of Bushbuckridge, Mpumalanga.Councillor Mavis Ndlovu said: &ldquo;The fourth teen died shortly after arriving at Tintswalo Hospital. The kids were pupils at Malwana Primary, Mdluli Secondary and Mugena High schools.&rdquo; Angry Mpumalanga community safety liaison MEC, Petrus Ngomane, cops, provincial police commissioner Lieutenant-General Mondli Zuma, station commanders and municipal and liquor board officials raided the tavern and closed it.&ldquo;The tavern did not have a licence. All the liquor stock was removed from the tavern,&rdquo; said Ngomane.He added that the 23-year-old driver was found to have been under the influence of alcohol and had no driver&rsquo;s licence. &ldquo;The car belonged to the suspect&rsquo;s brother-in-law. &ldquo;He will appear in the Mhala Magistrates Court on charges of culpable homicide soon. &ldquo;We will ensure that the bereaved families receive assistance from the Road Accident Fund and help with the mass funeral,&rdquo; said Ngomane.